Games-Othello

This module is used to model a game of Othello in Perl.  This does not actually
allow you to play a game of Othello.  It is only a toolkit that may be used by
game designers that wish to focus purely on the interface and leave the game
logic up to something else.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Games::Othello

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Games-Othello

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Games-Othello

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Games-Othello

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Games-Othello

